       <td valign=top width=305>


       <font size=+2 face="Arial", "Helvetica"><STRONG>HP's got some work to do</STRONG></font>

        <br>

        
<font size=-1 face="Arial", "Helvetica">
        By <a href="mailto:letters@news.com">
			 Reuters</a><BR>

        
	
	
	
		October 2, 1996, 4:30 p.m. PT
		</font>


    <p>

    <font  face="Times">





<a href="http://www.hp.com/">Hewlett-Packard</a> <a href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=HWP">(HWP)</a> is working to improve its inventory management and reduce sales channel inventories but still has a task ahead, according to Robert Wayman, executive vice president and chief financial officer.<p>

Wayman, speaking to investors at a <a href="http://www.montgomery.com/">Montgomery Securities</a> investment conference, said the company has been pleased with progress in financial management, but he labeled inventory management as "the notable exception."<p>

"All in all, we're very pleased with the progress that we've made," he said of HP's ability to respond to changing market conditions.<p>

"&#91;In&#93; inventory management, we've been struggling as we're dealing with how to deal with flat growth and long, complicated supply chains," he added.<p>

Wayman noted that in the retail channel, the company needed to build higher levels of inventory ahead of new product launches to meet subsequent customer demand.<p>

"For example, when we introduce a new PC or printer, the expectation is that we should have about 200,000 products ready to ship at the time of the product announcement," he said, noting HP was seeking to make improvements.<p>

"While we haven't entirely turned the corner on inventory, we have slowed the growth significantly in the third quarter," he told investors.<p>

"During that period, we have been working with our channel partners to reduce their inventory levels as well, even if that resulted in canceling outstanding orders in some instances," he said, without elaborating on the extent of cancellations.<p>

<p><font size=-1><a href="/copyright_reuters.html">Copyright</A> &#169; 1996 <A HREF="http://www.reuters.com">Reuters Limited</a>. All rights reserved.</font>
</font>

        </td>

<td width=5 rowspan=1>
</td>



     


      <td valign=top width=155>

<A HREF="javascript:OpenWindow();"onMouseOver="window.status='Desktop news'; return true" onMouseOut="window.status=''; return true"><img src="/Graphics/dtn_desktop.gif" width=155 height=70 border=0></a>

        <p>




       


        



