<h1 align="center"><b>Programme for the Twinning of Rhodes and
Visby</b></h1>

<p align="center"><a href="../rhodos-gotland/index.htm"
target="_top"><font size="4"><strong>News</strong></font></a><font
size="4"><strong> from the twinning week</strong> (in swedish)</font></p>

<hr>

<h2><b>Sunday 22/9</b></h2>

<p><em><strong>21.30</strong></em><br>
Arrival of delegation from Sweden.<br>
Welcome at airport. </p>

<h2><b>Monday 23/9</b></h2>

<p>Morning Free </p>

<p>Afternoon Free </p>

<p><em><strong>18.00</strong></em><br>
Opening of Photographic Exhibition in the foyer of the National
Theatre. </p>

<p><em><strong>19.00</strong></em><br>
Opening of Goland Art Exhibition Rodiaki Epavil. </p>

<p><em><strong>20.00</strong></em><br>
Opening of Handicraft Exhibition Rodiaki Epavil.<br>
Reception in the Rodiaki Epavil with music provided by the
Gotlandsmusiken Jazz Ensamble. </p>

<p><em><strong>22.00</strong></em><br>
Music by the Sax Quartet of the Gotlandsmusiken at the Akation. </p>

<h2><b>Tuesday 24/9</b></h2>

<p><em><strong>12.00</strong></em><br>
Press Conference in the Municipal Council Chamber of the Town
Hall . </p>

<p>Afternoon Free. </p>

<p><em><strong>17.50</strong></em><br>
Arrival of guests at the Castello accompanied by Knights and
mounted guards - the Swedish delegation will be wearing medival
costumes. </p>

<p><em><strong>18.00</strong></em><br>
Opening of Gotland Exhibition, Castello. </p>

<p><em><strong>19.00</strong></em><br>
Twinning Cermon, Castello.<br>
Signing of the Twinning Protocol. </p>

<p><em><strong>20.00</strong></em><br>
Reception in the Castello, with music by the group Visby
Vaganter. </p>

<p><em><strong>21.30</strong></em><br>
Piano Recital by Tasos Venetoklis and Staffan Scheja in the
Castello Courtyard. </p>

<h2><b>Wednesday 25/9</b></h2>

<p><em><strong>10.00</strong></em><br>
Informative meeting chaired by the Mayor of Rhodes concerning the
structure and running of the Town Hall of Rhodes. </p>

<p><em><strong>13.00</strong></em><br>
Lunch at the OTE Club with representatives of the Municipality. </p>

<p>Afternoon Free. </p>

<p><em><strong>20.00</strong></em><br>
Joint performance by the Gotland Choir and the Childrens and
Experimental Choir of Rhodes at the Rodon Cinema. </p>

<p><em><strong>22.00</strong></em><br>
Consert by the Gotlandsmusiken Jazz Ensamble at the Akation. </p>

<h2><b>Thursday 26/9</b></h2>

<p><em><strong>10.00</strong></em><br>
Meeting to discuss cultural matters at the Rodiaki Epavli. </p>

<p>Afternoon Free. </p>

<p><em><strong>18.00</strong></em><br>
Puppet Theatre from Gotland and Karayozi Puppet Theatre from
Rhodes at the Akation, Mandraki. </p>

<p><em><strong>20.00</strong></em><br>
The Visby Vaganter and the Gotland Choir will give a performance
at the Church of Santa Maria. </p>

<p><em><strong>20.00</strong></em><br>
Reception at the Castello on the occasion of the <a
href="programme-96sept.htm">inauguration of the International
Writers and Translators Centre of Rhodes</a>. </p>

<p><em><strong>21.00</strong></em><br>
Musical performance by the Municipal Brass Band of Rhodes and the
Big Brass Band Gotlandsmusiken, Troullos, Mandraki. </p>

<h2><b>Friday 27/9 - </b><font size="4"><em>World Tourism Day</em></font></h2>

<p><em><strong>10.00</strong></em><br>
Informative meeting and discussion concerning sporting matters at
the Municipal Sports and Youth Organisation ( DONA ), followed by
meeting with members of the Municipal Hygiene Company ( DEK ). </p>

<p><em><strong>13.00</strong></em><br>
Lunch with the members of DONA/DEK. </p>

<p>Afternoon Free. </p>

<p>19.00 Concert by the Gotlandsmusiken in 100 Palms Square. </p>

<p><em><strong>20.30</strong></em><br>
Pop concert by the Swedish group Hedningarna and the Greek group
Magic di Spell in the Town Hall Square. </p>

<h2><b>Saturday 28/9</b> </h2>

<p><em><strong>10.00</strong></em><br>
Departure from City Tour </p>

<p>Afternoon free </p>

<p><em><strong>18.00</strong></em><br>
Procession of Knights and musicial performance by the group PAX
in the Old Town (Socratous St. and Ippokrates Square) </p>

<p><em><strong>20.00</strong></em><br>
<i>The Sax quartet of the Gotlandsmusik will perfom at the
Akation</i> </p>

<p><em><strong>20.45</strong></em><br>
Depature for the reception at Rodini with nusic privided by the
Gotlandsmusiken, followed by traditional Greek music and dances. </p>

<p>Return to hotel by bus.</p>

<h2><b>Sunday 29/9</b> </h2>

<p><em><strong>10.00</strong></em><br>
Departure from the front of the Town Hall for boat excursion to
Kalithea </p>

<p><em><strong>23.00</strong></em><br>
Departure from Rhodes airport</p>

