<h2>Re: Alone in cyberspace?</h2>
<!--webbot bot="FormInsertHere"
descr="The FormInsertHereBot indicates the point in an HTML file where you want a SaveResultsBot, Registration, or DiscussionBot to insert new results."
startspan --><!--webbot bot="FormInsertHere" endspan
i-checksum="0" -->

<p><b>Category: </b>General<br>
<b>From: </b>rowan@ix.netcom.com<br>
<b>Date: </b>28 nov 1996<br>
<b>Time: </b>19:51:14<br>
<b>Remote Name: </b>204.32.164.83<br>
</p>

<h3>Comments</h3>

<p>This is a burningly important article. I read Clifford Stoll's
book as well, and highly recommend it. </p>

<p> The issues I would like to put forward is that of true
internet publishing, i.e., edited, publishing of high quality
prose and poetry. Publising that can match that of print in
relevance and quality. </p>

<p> How do we achieve it? How do we replace books? Do we want to
replace books? </p>

<p> I think the Internet is the perfect forum for the aspiring or
even established writer, but how do you &quot;get heard&quot; in
the galaxy of noise? </p>

<p> Rowan Wolf </p>
