<html>

<head>
<title>Bilim Dilinde Krtler ve Krdistan</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p><b>Original title:</b> Bilim Dilinde Krtler ve Krdistan <br>
<b>English title:</b> Kurds and Kurdistan in the language of
science <br>
<b>Swedish title:</b> Kurder och Kurdistan i vetenskapens sprk <br>
<b>Author:</b> Edip Polat<br>
<b>Original language:</b> Turkish<br>
<b>Publishing house:</b> Doz Yayinlari<br>
<b>Publishing country:</b> Ankara / Turkey<br>
<b>Publishing year:</b> December 1992</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE BOOK<br>
</b>In the book <i>Flora in Turkey, </i>in ten volumes, the
plants that have been presented through botanic studies by
several scientist sare treated. The denominations for the plants
are in Latin. Words are to be found that georaphiccaly asociates
the country of origin to Kurdistan.<br>
The Turkish universitys change the names with Latin extraction
only beacuse the name &quot;Kurd&quot; or &quot;Kurdistan&quot;
occurs. <br>
This is a divergent attitude towards the scientific work and
denominations of such, a fact that the Turkish universitys dont
care a bit about. <br>
Edip Polat, who himself is a biologist, maps the eliminated
plant-names and presents them for the reader.<br>
He criticizes the attitude of the &quot;scientific
institutions&quot; in Turkey and consider these as a proof of the
politics that is pursued against the Kurdish people.</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE AUTHOR<br>
</b>Edip Polat (b. 1962 in Bismil) studied biology in the
Diyarbakir University. After beeing in prison in Diyarbakir, he
wrote his first book: <i>Diyarbakir Geregi</i> (The Diyabakir
Reality), <br>
He was sentenced to 3 months of imprisonmet by the Court of State
Security in Ankara in 1990 for his book.<br>
In 1991 he published <i>Nevrozladik Safaklari</i> (We made Newroz
of the Dawn), which gave him a 2 year sentence and a 50.000.000
TL fine in 1993.<br>
In December 1992 he published <i>Bilim Dilinde Krtler ve
Krdistan</i> (Kurds and Kurdistan in the language of science).
In connection with the publishing he was charged with a years
imprisonment and a 100 million TL fine.<br>
In a manuscript with the title <i>&quot;Is it Science or the
Official Ideology?&quot;,</i> which was taken in charge when he
was in prison, also resulted in a new sentence: 1 year of
inprisonment and a 100 million TL fine. An appeal against the
verdict has been made to the Supreme Court.</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE LAWSUIT AGAINST THE BOOK<br>
Instance:</b> The State Security Court in Ankara<br>
<b>Crime:</b> For making propoganda &quot;against the state,
country and the indivisible unity of the nation&quot;.<br>
<b>Date of judgement:</b> December 1992<br>
<b>Date of arrest:</b> He was allready in prison.<br>
<b>The Verdict:</b> 1 year of inprisonment and a 100 million TL
fine, according to the 8:th paragraph, nr. 3713 in the law &quot;
The Anti-terror Law&quot;, and the ban of the book.<br>
Polat was in prison in various times. </p>

