<html>

<head>
<title>Bitlisli Kemal Fevzi ve Krt rgtleri Iindeki Yeri</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p><b>Original title:</b> Bitlisli Kemal Fevzi ve Krt
rgtleri Iindeki Yeri<br>
<b>English title: </b>Kemal Fevzi from Bitlis and his role within
Kurdish organisations<br>
<b>Swedish title:</b> Kemal Fevzi frn Bitlis och hans roll inom
kurdiska organisationer<br>
<b>Author:</b> Malmsamij [Mehmet Tayfun]<br>
<b>Original language:</b> Turkish<br>
<b>Publishing house:</b> Firat Yayinlari<br>
<b>Country of Publishing:</b> Istanbul / Turkey<br>
<b>Publishing year:</b> December 1993</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE BOOK<br>
</b>The book is about Kemal Fevzi (1891 or 1892 - 1925) from
Bitlis and his role within Kurdish organisations. The author
studies old documents, media and other sources of information ni
order to inform the reader about Kemals cultural and political
work. <br>
Kemal Fevzi studied in the Military Academy in Istanbul and
finished his studies in 1912. He joined the Balcan war that same
year. <br>
He made his debute with a collection of poems and continued his
authorship by writing poetry as well as political articels.<br>
In the 1920's he participated in different Kurdish student
organisations like <i>Hv</i> (The Hope) [1912], <i>Kurdistan
Muhibban Cemiyeti</i> (Beloved Kurdistan Society) [1912] and in
the editorial staffs in periodicals like the first
exile-publication <i>Kurdistan</i> and <i>Jin</i> (The Life).<br>
The Sheikh Said rebellion in 1925 ends in the execution of
several Kurdish leaders. Kemal Fevzi is among them. He is
executed together with other Kurdish leaders accused of the
crimes &quot;for striving to found a free Kurdistan and treason
against the Turkish Republic&quot; in May 25, 1925, in
Diyarbakir. </p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE AUTHOR<br>
</b>Malmsanij, the author of the book, has been living in
Sweden for14 years. He worked as a teacher in Turkey.<br>
In 1978 together with other colleuges, Malmsanij formed the
Kurdish litterary periodical Tirej, the first of its kind in that
part of Kurdistan.<br>
He is one of the pioneers that started to work with the Kurdish
dialect Dimili (Zazaki). <br>
To this time of date he has published several books in Kurdish in
both Kurmandji and Dimili (Zaza) dialects, as well as Turkish
books. <br>
Today he is the president of the Kurdish Writers Association in
Sweden, which was founded in January 22, 1995.</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE LAWSUIT AGAINST THE BOOK<br>
Instance:</b> The State Security Court nr. 5 in Istanbul <br>
<b>Prosecutor:</b> Isa Geyik (18542)<br>
<b>Chairman:</b> Nazif Efe (15086)<br>
<b>The defendant:</b> Sleyman Yasar (Firat Publishinghouse in
Istanbul)<br>
<b>Crime:</b> For making propoganda against the state, country
and the indivisible unity of the nation.<br>
<b>Date of Judgement:</b> April 11, 1995<br>
<b>The Verdict:</b> 6 months of imprisonment and a 41.666.666 TL
fine, according to the 8:th paragraph, nr. 3713 in the law -
&quot;The Anti-terror Law&quot;, and the ban of the book. </p>

