<html>

<head>
<title>Paradigmanin Iflasi</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body>

<p><b>Original title:</b> Paradigmanin Iflasi<br>
<b>English title:</b> The Bancruptcy of the Paradigm<br>
<b>Swedish title:</b> Paradigmens konkurs<br>
<b>Author:</b> Prof. Fikret Baskaya<br>
<b>Original language:</b> Turkish<br>
<b>Publishing house:</b> Doz Yayinlari<br>
<b>Country of Publishing:</b> Istanbul / Turkiet<br>
<b>Publishing year:</b> April1991<br>
</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE BOOK<br>
</b><i>The Bancruptcy of the Paradigm</i> is a study by Baskaya
whish he refers to as &quot;an instruction to the criticism of
the official idiology&quot;.<br>
His studies concerning imperialism, underdevelopment and
questions about transitory stages from capitalism to socialism in
the universitys of Paris and Poitier, resulted in many books. <br>
In his last book Baskaya discusses questions like &quot;the
national struggle&quot; as a rhetorical account of Atatrks
politics. <br>
He underlines the bancruptcy of exactly that policy when it comes
to the Kurdish matter and the national eonomy.<br>
</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE AUTHOR<br>
</b>Prof. Fikret Baskaya (b. 1940 in Denizli) studied economy at
the University of Ankara. He went on with his studies concerning
imperialism, underdevelopment and questions about transitory
stages from capitalism to socialism in the universitys of Paris
and Poitier. <br>
He published several books which dealt with different economical
questions.<br>
He works at the Gazi University in Bolu. Baskaya cooperates in
the daily paper Demokrasi which began its distribution a couple
of months ago in Ankara.<br>
</p>

<p><b>ABOUT THE LAWSUIT AGAINST THE BOOK<br>
Instance:</b> The State Security Court in Ankara<br>
<b>Crime:</b> For making propoganda against the state, country
and the indivisible unity of the nation.<br>
<b>Date of Judgement:</b> 18 March 1994<br>
<b>Date of arrest:</b> 18 March 1994<br>
<b>The Verdict:</b> 20 months of imprisonment and a 41.666.666 TL
fine, according to the 8:th <br>
paragraph, nr. 3713 in the law - &quot;The Anti-terror Law&quot;,
and the ban of the book.<br>
Baskaya was in prison in Haymana. He was released Juli 14, 1995. </p>

