<html>

<head>
<title>Baltic Centre for Writers and Translators - Presentation</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="images/bakgr.gif" link="#800019" vlink="#4B4D4C">
<p align=center><img src="images/nyovlog.gif" align=bottom width=286 height=165></p>
<p><img src="images/prick.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20> <font size=5>The Centre is for professional writers and translators</font><br>
of literary fiction from the countries round the Baltic Sea, Norway and Iceland. If you can 
indicate a definite project, you can stay here free of charge for up to a month.</p>
<p>The Baltic Centre for Writers and Translators is a concrete result of the Writers&#180;cruise, 
Baltic Waves, which assembled 300 writers and translators on the same boat on the Baltic. 
The cruise also resulted in the Baltic Writers&#180; Council, which has the ultimate responsibility 
for all activities at this joint Centre. The Centre consists of two buildings in central Visby and 
is financed by the County of Gotland and Gotland Municipality. The governing board of the 
Centre includes representatives of Gotland County Council, Gotland Municipality, The 
Swedish Writers&#180; Union and The Baltic Writers&#180; Council.</p>
<p><img src="images/prick.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20> <font size=5>Visby within the walls</font> </p>
<table COLSPEC="L20 L20">
<tr><td>is characteristically mediaeval. The Centre is right in the middle 
of the town, in a quiet place with a wonderful view. Close to are 
a chemist&#180;s, shops of all kinds, the County Library, the Museum 
of Art and the Historical Museum. The wine store and the 
Gotland College of Higher Education are within a few minutes&#180; 
walking distance and close to are the lovely shore walk, good 
cycle tracks and bathing. It is easy to get round the island by 
local bus or hired car.<p>Visby is one of the most popular holiday resorts in Sweden and 
during the summer months, life and entertainment are fairly busy. 
In the autumn, winter and spring, life is calmer, and peace and 
quiet to work is easy to find. </p>
</td><td><img src="images/gul.JPG" align=bottom width=170 height=201></td></tr>
</table>
<p>It is also easy to make contact with people here. There are opportunities for holding lectures 
at the library and the College, to meet students etc. We would be pleased to negotiate 
contacts.</p>
<p><img src="images/prick.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20> <font size=5>A great many activities</font><br>
meetings and seminars, workshops and poetry festivals are arranged at the centre for people 
in the Baltic area who work within literature.</p>
<p><img src="images/prick.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20> <font size=5>The Centre has eleven rooms</font><br>
of which four are double rooms, all with a shower and a view of the town and the sea. 
(Sheets, towels etc included.) Typewriters, computers (Macintosh and PC), laser printers, 
fax and telephone. Communal well equipped kitchen for self-catering. Library under 
construction, including the most important dictionaries and reference books in relevant 
languages. Television room, common room for about twenty-five people, laundry and sauna. 
Bicycles on loan.</p>
<p><img src="images/prick.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20> <font size=5>Residence is free</font><br>
but the cost of your journey depend on how you come here, by air or sea. Visby has daily 
sea connections with Nyn&auml;shamn and Oskarshamn, and many flights every day to a few 
destinations on the mainland. In summer communications are more numerous and more 
frequent. Your stay need not cost a great deal if you cook your own food. Otherwise there 
are a number of eating places nearby.</p>
<p><img src="images/prick.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20> <font size=5>A number of grants</font><br>
are awarded each year by the board of the Centre. The total sum is intended to cover the 
journey and a month&#180;s stay. There are various possibilities of grants and funds in each 
country. Contact your Authors&#180; Union or our office for further information.</p>
<p><img src="images/prick.gif" align=bottom width=20 height=20> <font size=5>Contact us</font><br>
if you wish to know more about the Centre or require application forms. Welcome!</p>
<p>Address: &Ouml;stersj&ouml;ns F&ouml;rfattar- och &Ouml;vers&auml;ttarcentrum, Box 1096, 621 21 Visby, Sweden.<br>
Telephone: Gunilla Fors&eacute;n +46 498 21 87 64, Annette Glover +46 498 21 83 85.<br>
Fax: +46 498 21 87 98.<br>
The office is open Monday - Friday 9-5.</p>
<p align=center>For topical information on communications and ticket prices, contact <a href="http://www.gotlandica.se/gotland/tuservice/homepage.htm">Gotland&#180;s Tourist 
Service</a>, &Ouml;sterport, 621 45 Visby, Sweden.<br>
Telephone: +46 498 20 60 00.</p>
</body>

</html>
