<html>

<head>
<title>Baltic Centre for Writers and Translators - Future projects</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="images/bakgr.gif" link="#800019" vlink="#4B4D4C">
<div align=center><center>
<table COLSPEC="L20 L20">
<tr><td><img src="images/OVCENTRU.GIF" align=bottom width=180 height=137></td><td><font size=6>B</font><font size=5>ALTIC </font><font size=6>C</font><font size=5>ENTRE FOR<br>
</font><font size=6>W</font><font size=5>RITERS AND </font><font size=6>T</font><font size=5>RANSLATORS</font></td></tr>
</table>
</center></div>
<hr>
<h2 align=center>Future projects</h2>
<p>The Baltic Centre for Writers and Translators arranges the <strong>III International Poetry</strong> 
Festival on Gotland 13 - 16 June 1996. Poets and translators from mainly the Baltic region 
like Wislawa Szymborska and Bronislaw Maj (Poland), Sigitas Geda and Nijol&eacute; 
Miliauskait&eacute; (Lithuania), Guntars Godins (Latvia), Bo Carpelan and Jarkko Laine (Finland). 
From Iceland Steinunn Sigurdard&oacute;ttir, from Bulgaria Blaga Dimitrova and from Romania 
Ileana Malancioiu. Among the Swedish participants are Agneta Pleijel, Marie Lundquist, 
Lasse S&ouml;derberg, Magnus Nilsson and also two poets with a more exotic background like 
Gabriela Melinescu and Li Li.<br>
Altogether there will be some 30 participants and seven public readings all over the island 
during the four days and nights the festival is going on. There will also be a strong element of 
music and singing in the programme.</p>
<p>For more information please contact The Baltic Centre for Writers and Translators tel 
+46-498-218764, fax +46-498-218798 or e-mail <a href="mailto:baltic.centre@gotlandica.se">baltic.centre@gotlandica.se</a></p>
<p><strong>&quot;Writing for Cinema&quot;</strong> is a project arranged by the Centre in collaboration with the 
County Administration on Gotland 1 - 4 September 1996. To this seminar the organizers 
want to invite writers and people active in the world of cinema from the Baltic Region. The 
purpose will be to discuss the specific problems connected with writing for cinema and after 
the seminar there will be a possibility for the participants to take part in the Baltic Film 
Festival in Burgsvik, on southern Gotland.</p>
<p>For more information contact Elisabet Edlund, County Administration, 621 85 Visby tel 
+46-498-292071, e-mail: <a href="mailto:elisabet.edlund@cobalt.se">elisabet.edlund@cobalt.se</a> or Gunilla Fors&eacute;n, The Baltic Centre, 
Visby, tel +46-498-218764, e-mail <a href="mailto:baltic.centre@gotlandica.se">baltic.centre@gotlandica.se</a></p>
<p>The Conference <a href="http://www.gotlandica.se/summit96/freedom/freedom.htm"><strong>Freedom of Expression-Information-Libraries</strong></a> will take place in Visby 
May 3 - 4 1996 for Politicians, Cultural Affairs Directors, Writers and Librarians - at the 
same time as the <a href="http://www.gotlandica.se/summit96/index.htm"><strong>Baltic Sea States Summit</strong></a>.</p>
<p>This conference want to put the focus on the Freedom of Expression in the post communist 
world and the role of librarians in a democratic society. Wellknown writers from the Baltic 
region like Jaan Kaplinski, Estonia, Andrei Bitov, Russia, and Adam Michnik, Poland will 
participate in a panel discussion.</p>
<p>For more information, please contact Barbro Ejendal, Kultur- och Fritidsf&ouml;rvaltningen, 
S-621 81 Visby, tel +46-498-269651, fax +46-498-269659.</p>
</body>

